---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Transparency"
  description="What The Well does and does not log, store, or share."
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl mb-6">Transparency</h1>
  <p class="mb-4">
    The Well is operated with a deliberately narrow read path. This page
    summarizes what the site does and does not do. See
    <a
      href="https://github.com/thewell/thewell/blob/main/docs/anonymity.md"
      rel="noopener">docs/anonymity.md</a>
    in the repository for the full threat model.
  </p>
  <h2 class="text-xl mt-8 mb-3">What we do not do</h2>
  <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
    <li>We do not publish subjective opinions about judges.</li>
    <li>We do not log IP addresses on contributor-facing endpoints.</li>
    <li>We do not run analytics or session replay on those pages.</li>
    <li>
      We do not link specific contributions to specific contributors,
      architecturally.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h2 class="text-xl mt-8 mb-3">What we do</h2>
  <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
    <li>Judge pages are pre-rendered static HTML with no client-side JS.</li>
    <li>
      The site is served from Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare's edge logs apply;
      we do not add analytics on top.
    </li>
    <li>
      Every field on a judge page is sourced, with links to the underlying
      court document or the contribution record.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h2 class="text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Governance</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">
    See the <a href="/canary/">warrant canary</a> for the current status of
    legal process against Zachary Brenner.
  </p>
</Base>
